<p>Under tort law a prima facie case of <strong>NONDISCLOSURE</strong> (or CONCEALMENT) requires showing 1) a <strong>DUTY</strong> to <strong>disclose</strong> material <strong>facts</strong>, 2) <strong>BREACH</strong> of that duty, 3) <strong>REASONABLE RELIANCE</strong> by the plaintiff on facts as they appeared to be, and 4) <strong>INJURY CAUSED </strong>by the nondisclosure.</p>
